               <p>THOMAS ALEXANDER LOFTUS. I am a <rs id="t18330905-90-viclabel518" type="occupation">clerk in the law</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18330905-90-victim928 t18330905-90-viclabel518"></join>. I was standing at the corner of <placeName id="t18330905-90-crimeloc519">Giltspur-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18330905-90-crimeloc519" type="placeName" value="Giltspur-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18330905-90-crimeloc519" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18330905-90-off516 t18330905-90-crimeloc519"></join>, between twelve and one o'clock, on the 2nd of September; I felt a tug at my pocket, and turned round and saw the prisoner close to me - I seized him, and accused him of taking my handkerchief - he denied it - I looked behind him and saw it - I took it and him; this is it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18330905-90-person929">
                  ARTHUR 
                  WINDSOR
               <interp inst="t18330905-90-person929" type="surname" value="WINDSOR"></interp>
